# Signoff Rule Bible (authoritative)

The single source of truth for every Kompass signoff build. If any other doc,
skill, or memory conflicts with this file, **this file wins**. The builder lives in
the `flow-automation` repo at `signoff_builder/signoff-builder` (config `config.yaml`,
design `docs/SPEC.md`); this repo holds the per-period run scripts under `scripts/`.
Keep this file in sync with `flow-automation/.cursor/rules/signoff-rule-bible.mdc`.

## Eligibility — what is even a signoff candidate

A tracker row is eligible for cross-reference checks AND for signoff sheets only when:

- the `complete` column is **blank**, OR
- the `complete` column says **`No`** AND the `comment` column is **empty**.

Everything else is decided and routed **OFF** (never team, never REVIEW):

- `complete = No` **with a comment** → a human already resolved it → OFF.
- `complete = Yes` → trusted complete → OFF.

## Routing

- **Week is not a team gate.** Eligible rows incomplete in both PROD and SI go to
  the team signoff regardless of fiscal week.
- Cross-reference status routes eligible rows into supervisor-action buckets:
  `Complete in PROD`, `Complete in SI`, `Mark Done on Tracker` (complete in both),
  `Vendor - On Manifest`.
- Tracker/system contradictions and lossless-backstop rows go to the validation
  REVIEW list — never silently dropped.

## District supervisor routing — D6 ONLY

- **Only District 6 gets dedicated supervisor sheets/packages.** Config key:
  `supervisor_routing_districts: [6]`.
- **Every other district (D1, D8, D9, …) folds supervisor-action rows** (grocery/gm,
  blitz, vendor/manifest, confirm in SI/PROD) **into its own regular team signoff**.
  No separate supervisor package for non-D6 districts.
- D6 supervisor sheets use the same new 5-master template as team sheets.

## Test-set stores — D6 286 & 163

- Config key: `test_set_keep_on_signoff_stores: ["163", "286"]`.
- For these stores, any set **complete in BOTH PROD and SI** must **stay on the team
  signoff** (its completion flags are cleared) instead of routing to `Mark Done on
  Tracker` / a Complete-in-both confirm sheet. Test sets physically carry ~2 weeks
  but must be signed off **every week**.
- Only the both-complete case is overridden; PROD-only / SI-only still route normally.

## Formatting / template fidelity

- Use the **5-master template**. Copy **all** formatting — borders, merged cells,
  exact row heights, fills — when resizing/populating data bands.
- **Signature panel borders:** horizontal separators between rows + the exterior box
  outline ONLY. **No interior vertical borders** splitting the label/value columns.
  Implemented by `clear_interior_verticals` (styles.py) /
  `_clear_signature_panel_verticals` (builder.py); never reintroduce them.
- Signature blocks are **dynamic** — lines follow the active departments.

## Output & delivery

- Dump-bin drop is tied to `--export-pdf`, **independent of `--email`**. For manual
  emailing, omit `--email`; team PDFs still land in the weekly Dump Bin.
- Team folders `.../2026 Dump Bin/Kompass/Period ## .../P##W# .../Signoffs/District N/`
  contain **team PDFs only** — no `.xlsx`/`.json`/`.csv`/temp and no
  `P##W#_Supervisor_D#_...pdf` packages.
- **File output versioning:** never overwrite or crash on a locked file. Bump to
  `... version 2.pdf` (see `file-output-versioning` rule / `src/lib/file-utils.js`).

## Store-number matching

- Match store numbers as **whole numbers** after normalizing leading zeros. `28` must
  not match `281`/`128`. Never trust upstream substring `store_number=` filters.
  (See `sas-exact-store-number` rule.)

## Cross-reference refresh

- Live in-process refresh can deadlock (python → node → morning-auth) when the SAS
  session needs re-auth. For reliable batch runs: refresh out-of-band
  (`node scripts/refresh_signoff_crossrefs.mjs`), then set
  `cross_reference.auto_refresh = false` and point `paths.prod_completion_dir` /
  `paths.si_completion_dir` at `C:/SignoffBuilder/cross-reference-cache/{prod,si}`.
  The `scripts/p06w2-signoff-*.py` runners in this repo follow that pattern.

